significant and weak proportion of variance (R2 = 0.04, F(37, 479) = 0.59, p = 0.975, adj. R2 = -0.03). The model's
intercept, corresponding to month = 0, FFMC = 0, DMC = 0, DC = 0, ISI = 0, temp = 0, RH = 0, wind = 0 and rain = 0, is at
-197.43 (95% CI [-1088.66, 693.79], t(479) = -0.44, p = 0.664). Within this model:

Intervals (CIs) and p-values were computed using a Wald t-distribution approximation.
